## Rules
- Start with `create_file_manifest(repo_path)` (ignore-aware, safe)
- Never run `tree` on repo root (token overflow risk)
- Prefer tools over shell: `rg_search`, `repomix_*`, `read_file_bounded`
- Shell commands: non-interactive, bounded (`head -N`), quick
- ALWAYS use `read_file_bounded` to read a file before writing or modifying it
- GitNexus workflow: `gitnexus_query` → `gitnexus_context` → `gitnexus_impact`
- Evidence format: `path/file.ext:line` + symbol + confidence
- Diagrams: ALWAYS use mermaid code fences — never ASCII art or box-drawing characters

## Tool Orchestration
Use GitNexus and git tools to surface structural insights:

```mermaid
graph LR
  subgraph DISCOVERY
    A1[gitnexus_query]
    A2[rg_search]
    A3[repomix_*]
  end
  subgraph GIT_CONTEXT[GIT CONTEXT]
    B1[git_hotspots]
    B2[git_cochanged]
    B3[git_blame]
    B4[git_history]
  end
  subgraph GITNEXUS[GITNEXUS ANALYSIS]
    C1[gitnexus_context]
    C2[gitnexus_impact]
    C3[gitnexus_detect_changes]
    C4[gitnexus_cypher]
  end
  subgraph OUTPUTS
    D1[CONTEXT.md]
    D2[FILE_INDEX.md]
    D3[files.business]
    D4[CONTEXT.bundle]
  end
  DISCOVERY --> GIT_CONTEXT --> GITNEXUS --> OUTPUTS
```

GitNexus adds value when you need:
- Symbol relationships (gitnexus_context) - find callers, callees, process participation
- Blast radius (gitnexus_impact) - assess what breaks if a symbol changes
- Domain search (gitnexus_query) - find code by concept or domain terms
- Custom queries (gitnexus_cypher) - structural queries beyond built-in tools

## Critical Tool Failures (FAST EXIT)
If a `gitnexus_*` tool returns an error status, report the error and attempt alternative tools (e.g., fall back to `rg_search` + `git_*` tools). Do NOT abandon the analysis entirely.
